&lt;h2&gt;District Transport Driver&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The District Transport Department for Portsmouth Hospitals University NHS Trust is looking for a driver to join a small, but busy department that invests in the community by providing a valuable transport service to the Trust and other NHS organisations both locally and across the South Coast.The department is responsible for maintaining scheduled collections/deliveries of clinical notes, post, pharmacy, clinical specimens and consumables, as well as ad hoc requests from the hospital, which may include the moving of equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to hold a Drivers CPC (Certificate of Professional Competence), and your licence must include full entitlement for categories C1 (HGV 3 up to 7.5 tonnes) and D1 (minibuses, up to 16 passenger seats) to be able to carry out the varied functions and requirements of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 11/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 20/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
